      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(embedding): restrict openai-compatible dimensions to api.openai.com to prevent connection resets on self-hosted servers",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes memory index stalling on \"batch start\" when using `openai-compatible` embedding provider with non-OpenAI servers (llama.cpp, Ollama, Alibaba, etc.).\n\n## Root cause\n\nThe `openai-compatible` embedding provider unconditionally sent the `dimensions` parameter (derived from `outputDimensionality` config) to every embedding server. The `dimensions` parameter is an OpenAI-specific feature supported only by `api.openai.com`. Sending it to self-hosted or third-party servers causes connection resets that trigger the memory embedding retry+split cascade, stalling indexing.\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. Restrict `dimensions` to api.openai.com only\n`src/plugins/openai-compatible-embedding-provider.ts` — The `postEmbeddingRequest` function now checks whether the baseUrl hostname is `api.openai.com` before including the `dimensions` parameter.\n\n### 2. Add max split depth guard\n`extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-embedding-policy.ts` — Added `EMBEDDING_SPLIT_MAX_DEPTH=4` to prevent exponential retry fan-out when connection errors affect all sub-batches.\n\n### 3. Add \"batch completed\" debug logs\n`extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager-embedding-ops.ts` — Added debug logs for parity with \"batch start\", improving observability.\n\n## Verification\n\n- 41 tests pass across 3 test files (policy, integration, provider)\n- TypeScript type check passes\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
